#: doc/src/docbkx/openstack-security/ch014_best-practices-for-operator-mode-access.xml:28
msgid ""
"As a cloud administrator, the dashboard provides an overall view of the size "
"and state of your cloud. You can create users and tenants/projects, assign "
"users to tenant/projects and set limits on the resources available for them."
msgstr ""

#: doc/src/docbkx/openstack-security/ch014_best-practices-for-operator-mode-access.xml:31
msgid ""
"The dashboard provides tenant-users a self-service portal to provision their "
"own resources within the limits set by administrators."
msgstr ""

#: doc/src/docbkx/openstack-security/ch014_best-practices-for-operator-mode-access.xml:34
msgid ""
"The dashboard provides GUI support for routers and load-balancers. For "
"example, Horizon now implements all of the main Neutron features."
msgstr ""

#: doc/src/docbkx/openstack-security/ch014_best-practices-for-operator-mode-access.xml:37
msgid ""
"It is an extensible Django web application that allows easy plug-in of third-"
"party products and services, such as billing, monitoring, and additional "
"management tools."
msgstr ""

#: doc/src/docbkx/openstack-security/ch014_best-practices-for-operator-mode-access.xml:40
msgid ""
"The dashboard can also be branded for service providers and other commercial "
"vendors."
msgstr ""

#: doc/src/docbkx/openstack-security/ch014_best-practices-for-operator-mode-access.xml:47
msgid ""
"Horizon requires cookies and JavaScript to be enabled in the web browser."
msgstr ""

#: doc/src/docbkx/openstack-security/ch014_best-practices-for-operator-mode-access.xml:50
msgid ""
"The web server that hosts Horizon should be configured for SSL to ensure "
"data is encrypted."
msgstr ""

#: doc/src/docbkx/openstack-security/ch014_best-practices-for-operator-mode-access.xml:53
msgid ""
"Both the Horizon web service and the OpenStack API it uses to communicate "
"with the back-end are susceptible to web attack vectors such as denial of "
"service and must be monitored."
msgstr ""

#: doc/src/docbkx/openstack-security/ch014_best-practices-for-operator-mode-access.xml:56
msgid ""
"It is now possible (though there are numerous deployment/security "
"implications) to upload an image file directly from a user’s hard disk to "
"Glance through Horizon. For multi-GB images it is still strongly recommended "
"that the upload be done using the Glance CLI"
msgstr ""

#: doc/src/docbkx/openstack-security/ch014_best-practices-for-operator-mode-access.xml:59
msgid ""
"Create and manage security groups through dashboard. The security groups "
"allows L3-L4 packet filtering for security policies to protect virtual "
"machines"
msgstr ""

